com.latencybusters.lbmct

Class LbmCtRcvConn

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcvConn

  • public class LbmCtRcvConn
extends java.lang.Object
    Connection object, mostly for internal use by CT. Application must NOT create, start, or stop this object directly; it is fully managed by CT internally. There are only two public APIs associated with this object: getRcvConnCbArg() and isHandshakeMessage(). Those APIs should only be called from inside the receiver callback.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods

      boolean isHandshakeMessage()

        public java.lang.Object getRcvConnCbArg()
        Retrieve the application-specific object associated with the connection, supplied by the application as the return value from LbmCtRcvConnCreateCallback.onRcvConnCreate(com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtRcv, com.latencybusters.lbmct.LbmCtPeerInfo, java.lang.Object).         Returns:

      • isHandshakeMessage

        public boolean isHandshakeMessage()
        Determine if a delivered message is a CT handshake message. Typically an application ignores CT handshake messages, except that they consume sequence numbers. This API can only be called synchronously from inside the receiver callback.
        Returns:
        True=delivered message is a CT handshake, false=delivered message is an application message.
